{
  "stem": "22972.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I mean, the concentration camps were going full blast in '37 and '38, before I left.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We saw people-- we knew of people who were arrested and who were beaten to death.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I-- I didn't witness-- I-- I once saw a man beaten.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I-- I saw people taken away.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But, I mean, everything else-- My mother's gynecologist was-- was married to a-- to a pure Aryan woman, and he refused to-- to divorce her.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He loved her.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And before they could get out of Germany-- he was set to get out-- he was beaten in his bed in front of her.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I overheard, when-- when she came crying and told my mother, that she never realized how much blood there was in the human being.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That there wasn't an-- an inch on the walls, and the ceiling, and floor that wasn't spattered with his blood.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But, you know-- so going to school and sitting there, not being able to talk?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My god, that was nothing.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Were you ever afraid for yourself or your family?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was afraid for my family.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was afraid in-- in-- in-- my God, in 1936, coming back from a trip to Italy-- 1935, I beg your pardon. '36, I would like to talk about that.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In 1935, we had been in Italy for the summer.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we came back and-- and-- it's a long story, but they took us-- they took my father and mother.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was a dumb thing that brought them in, but they took my-- my-- my-- mother and dad inside to be interrogated and left me alone in the car.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then I heard loud voices, and my mother crying, and my father yelling, and I was sure that any minute I would hear two shots.",
      "word_count": 26
    }
  ],
